A woman who lost her leg after the Boston Marathon bombings said goodbye to 2014 by walking for the first time.

Rebekah DiMartino, 27, had her left limb amputated in November as 17 operations and 19 months of physio failed to get her back on her feet.

Finally, on Wednesday, the beaming mother-of-one, from Katy, Texas, shared a video on Facebook of her first steps.

She plans to run the Boston Marathon in April 2015.

