'I am standing! Ahh!!' Ms DiMartino screamed in the hallway of OPA Prosthetics in Bellaire as KHOU filmed the momentous event.

'This is me walking, I have not walked in so long!'

Ms DiMartino was with her son Noah, now seven, and then-boyfriend, Pete DiMartino, at the finish line of the Boston Marathon in April 2013 when the two bombs detonated, killing three people and injuring 270.

All three were wounded in the blast but Rebekah suffered the most extensive damage to her left leg.

She had undergone 17 operations, including putting metal plates, screws and rods in her leg, and suffered a serious bone infection. 

